<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S21"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[270,475] s 21 Limitation on exemplary, punitive and aggravated damages">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CLAN02.S21" type="ext"/>[270,475]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Limitation on exemplary, punitive and aggravated damages</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>21</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>In an action for the award of personal injury damageswhere the act or omission that caused the injury or death was negligence, a court cannot award exemplary or punitive damages or damages in the nature of aggravated damages.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[s 21  subst Act 92 of 2002  s 3 and Sch 2, effective 6 December 2002]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
